<TITLE> M A Mannan buried </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Sep 22 (bdnews24.com)Former minister and Awami League advisory council member M A Mannan was buried on Tuesday in his family graveyard in the port city. His namaj-e-janaza was held at Jamiatul Falah Mosque after Asr prayers and a guard of honour. Mannan died of a heart attack in Chittagong on Monday after Eid prayers at age 73. Thousands of people gathered at the mosque to join the janaza and many placed flowers on his coffin draped in national bi-colours. Chittagong mayor A B M Mohiuddin Chowdhury, primary and mass education minister Afsarul Amin, former law minister Abdul Matin Khosru, former minister Mosharraf Hossain, Akhtaruzzaman Babu MP, ABM Fazlul Karim MP, former minister and BNP joint secretary general Abdullah Al Noman, former minister Amir Khosru Mahmood Chowdhury, Salahuddin Quader Chowdhury NP, AL presidium member Ataur Rahman Khan Kaiser and former state ministers Mir Nasir Uddin and Zafrul Islam Chowdhury were present, among others, in the janaza. His body was kept at the Chittagong Metropolitan AL's office before the janaza where many freedom fighters and political supporters gathered to pay their tributes. Mannan fought and organised the war of independence in 1971. He was elected to parliament in 1996. He also served as Chittagong City AL president and general secretary for many years. The veteran leader left six sons and two daughters. bdn
